In the Matter of Harold F. Cullen et al., Appellants-Respondents, v. James M. Power et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, Respondents, and Bernard Hirschhorn et al., Respondents-Appellants. Argued May 27, 1964; decided May 27, 1964. *762Richard A. Brown for appellants-respondents. Thomas Brian O’Connell for respondents-appellants.

No appearance for respondents.

Order affirmed, without costs; no opinion.

Concur: Chief Judge Desmond and Judges Dye, Fuld, Van Voorhis, Burke, Scileppi and Hamm*.

Designated pursuant to section 2 of article VI of the State Constitution in the temporary absence of Judge Bergan.
